%2Fcurrencies%2Frussia-frozen-assets-ukraine-war-weapon-finance-west-sanctions-eu-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Harvard%20negotiation%20expert%20thinks%20we%20need%20to%20embrace%20more%20conflict%20at%20work%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Businesswoman%20and%20businessman%20arguing%20in%20office%20passageway.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cdea13f533b039a883e26b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEmbracing%20conflict%20at%20work%20can%20increase%20job%20satisfaction%2C%20a%20negotiation%20expert%20says.%20%3Cp%3EWestend61%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Harvard%20negotiation%20expert%20advises%20people%20to%20embrace%20conflict%20at%20work%20to%20have%20better%20job%20satisfaction.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWilliam%20Ury%20told%20Forbes%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20productive%20work%20environment%20should%20not%20suppress%20conflict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEngaging%20in%20tough%20conversations%20with%20your%20boss%20or%20colleagues%20may%20help%20you%20reach%20your%20goals%20faster.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAvoiding%20conflict%20at%20work%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20sensible%20option%2C%20but%20a%20Harvard%20negotiation%20expert%20says%20this%20will%20lead%20to%20greater%20job%20dissatisfaction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Ury%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Harvard%20University's%20Program%20on%20Negotiation%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pon.harvard.edu%2Fshop%2Fgetting-to-yes-negotiating-agreement-without-giving-in%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3BGetting%20to%20Yes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20spoke%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fmelodywilding%2F2024%2F03%2F20%2Fhow-to-negotiate-for-anything-at-work-according-to-harvards-top-expert%2F%3Fsh%3D66da4b6c7d2e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EForbes%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20navigating%20and%20embracing%20workplace%20conflict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20often%20state%2C%20somewhat%20provocatively%2C%20that%20we%20actually%20need%20more%20conflict%20at%20work%2C%20specifically%20the%20kind%20that's%20constructive%E2%80%94what%20you%20might%20call%20'creative%20friction%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20Forbes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20as%20in%20healthy%20marriages%2C%20where%20partners%20don't%20shy%20away%20from%20issues%2C%20a%20productive%20work%20environment%20should%20not%20suppress%20conflict.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUry%20explained%20that%20people%20back%20away%20from%20conflicts%20because%20it%20makes%20them%20uncomfortable%2C%20but%20that%20this%20can%20ultimately%20make%20things%20worse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAvoidance%20doesn't%20resolve%20the%20underlying%20issues%20%E2%80%94%20it%20often%20makes%20them%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMy%20suggestion%20is%20counterintuitive%3A%20lean%20into%20the%20conflict%2C%20embrace%20it%2C%20and%20transform%20it.%20Instead%20of%20meeting%20conflict%20with%20animosity%2C%20we%20should%20approach%20it%20with%20curiosity%20to%20foster%20better%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUry%20offered%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20tackle%20difficult%20conversations%20with%20a%20boss%2C%20from%20asking%20for%20a%20raise%20to%20negotiating%20different%20work%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20avoiding%20tough%20conversations%20with%20your%20boss%2C%20which%20might%20lead%20to%20job%20dissatisfaction%20or%20even%20resignation%2C%20consider%20initiating%20a%20constructive%20dialogue%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUry%20suggests%20a%20strategy%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20to%20the%20balcony%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20involves%20taking%20a%20step%20back%20and%20understanding%20and%2