5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20tracking%20a%20pod%20of%20183%20killer%20whales%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20California%20is%20no%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20orcas%20found%20the%20perfect%20stage%20for%20an%20underwater%20ambush%3A%20a%20canyon%20in%20open%20water%20with%20steep%20walls%2C%20which%20they%20used%20to%20trap%20unsuspecting%20marine%20mammals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20surprising%20parts%20of%20the%20study%2C%26quot%3B%20Josh%20McInnes%2C%20a%20marine%20biologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20British%20Columbia%20in%20Canada%20and%20an%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Farticle%2F2423240-californian-orcas-used-specialised-tactics-for-hunting-whale-calves%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20Scientist%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrcas%20patrolling%20the%20canyon%20were%20seen%20honing%20in%20on%20gray%20whale%20mother-and-child%20pairs%2C%20trapping%20them%20against%20the%20canyon%20walls%20and%20chasing%20them%20until%20the%20calves%20became%20exhausted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20killer%20whales%20would%20then%20separate%20the%20calves%20from%20their%20mothers%20by%20body-blocking%20the%20parent%20and%20dragging%20the%20child%20toward%20open%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%20the%20orcas%20could%20call%20reinforcements%20to%20ram%20the%20calves%20with%20their%20noses%2C%20flip%20them%20in%20the%20air%2C%20or%20slam%20them%20with%20their%20tails.%20Per%20the%20study%2C%20the%20killer%20whales%20would%20often%20finish%20the%20calves%20off%20by%20jumping%20on%20top%20of%20their%20blowholes%2C%20pinning%20them%20underwater%20long%20enough%20to%20drown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ordeal%20lasted%20between%201-and-a-half%20and%205%20hours%2C%20after%20which%20the%20orcas%20would%20take%20turns%20feeding%20off%20the%20unfortunate%20calves'%20carcasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20behavior%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20unique%2C%20especially%20for%20this%20area%20at%20least%2C%26quot%3B%20McInnes%20said%2C%20per%20New%20Scientist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20constantly%20learning%20about%20killer%20whales.%20Every%20study%20that%20comes%20out%20is%20extremely%20valuable%20for%20our%20understanding%20of%20their%20ecology%20as%20well%20as%20their%20conservation%20needs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20McInnes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20the%20whales%20that%20fell%20prey%20to%20the%20orcas.%20Between%202006%20and%202021%2C%20the%20scientists%20found%20that%20elephant%20seals%2C%20minke%20whales%2C%20and%20dolphins%20were%20often%20on%20the%20menu%2C%20per%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0299291%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPLoS%20ONE%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOrca-hunting%20behaviors%20aren't%20just%20cool%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELearning%20about%20these%20animals'%20fascinating%20behaviors%20doesn't%20only%20satisfy%20scientific%20curiosity.%20It's%20crucial%20to%20understanding%20the%20complex%20puzzle%20shaping%20marine%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrevious%20studies%20have%20shown%20that%20even%20a%20few%20orcas%20picking%20up%20a%20new%20hunting%20behavior%20can%20entirely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Forca-kills-great-white-shark-south-africa-disrupt-fishing-industry-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereshape%20the%20local%20food%20chain%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20case%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20of%20two%20orcas%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20South%20Africa%20that%20chased%20away%20all%20the%20great%20white%20sharks%20from%20the%20Gansbaai%20coast.%20The%20big%20fish%20were%20scared%20off%20when%20the%20killer%20whales%20learned%20how%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-orca-sucking-out-shark-liver-left-die-