20the%20golden%20rule%20%E2%80%94%20treating%20others%20the%20way%20I%20want%20to%20be%20treated.%20Because%20knowing%20how%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20is%20almost%20always%20an%20exercise%20in%20empathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ERaising%20kids%20without%20entitlement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20question%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fteach-kids-appreciate-wealth-privilege-2022-1%5C%22%3Ea%20parent%20trying%20not%20to%20spoil%20their%20kids%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20their%20kids%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20financial%20privilege%20than%20the%20parent%20had%20growing%20up.%20It%20wasn't%20a%20stretch%20to%20empathize%20with%20this%20person%3B%20my%20story%20is%20quite%20similar.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20financially%20better%20off%20than%20my%20parents%20were%2C%20and%20because%20of%20this%2C%20my%20kids%20have%20more%20than%20I%20ever%20did%20at%20their%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20firsthand%20that%20the%20parent%20was%20likely%20experiencing%20two%20feelings%3A%20a%20genuine%20concern%20that%20too%20much%20privilege%20can%20lead%20to%20spoiled%20children%20and%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20personal%20envy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20nothing%20that%20forces%20us%20to%20face%20our%20childhood%20wounds%20quite%20like%20raising%20children.%20For%20the%20first%20time%2C%20we%20are%20in%20our%20parents'%20shoes%2C%20understanding%20the%20pressures%20that%20led%20them%20to%20make%20the%20decisions%20that%20would%20define%20our%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20this%2C%20I%20encouraged%20my%20reader%20to%20do%20something%20I%20strive%20to%20do%20with%20my%20children%3A%20Allow%20their%20childhood%20experience%20to%20inform%20how%20they%20raise%20their%20children%20without%20letting%20their%20scars%20interfere%20with%20that%20relationship.%20On%20a%20more%20concrete%20level%2C%20I%20also%20advised%20the%20reader%20to%20teach%20their%20kids%20gratitude%20at%20every%20turn%2C%20especially%20through%20the%20example%20they%20set.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorrying%20about%20kids'%20financial%20choices%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20all%20of%20the%20parents%20who%20are%20writing%20me%20are%20still%20raising%20their%20kids%20like%20I%20am.%20This%20is%20why%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20parent%20worried%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fson-wont-stop-wasting-money-mind-own-business-2023-12%5C%22%3Etheir%20son's%20purchase%20of%20a%20%2470%2C000%20pickup%20truck%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20drew%20my%20advice%20from%20my%20experience%20as%20a%20mother%20and%20as%20a%20daughter.%20I%20am%20all%20too%20familiar%20with%20how%20it%20feels%20to%20have%20parents%20lecturing%20me%20on%20my%20choices%20as%20a%2030-plus-year-old%20woman.%20It's%20always%20annoying%2C%20especially%20when%20they're%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20adult%20daughter%2C%20my%20advice%20was%20obvious%20%E2%80%94%20parents%20need%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20their%20adult%20children's%20financial%20affairs%20%E2%80%94%20but%2C%20as%20a%20mother%2C%20I%20know%20just%20how%20difficult%20that%20can%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20like%20to%20think%20that%20I%20will%20quit%20feeling%20so%20deeply%20invested%20in%20my%20children's%20experience%20of%20the%20world%20as%20they%20get%20older%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20likely.%20So%20I%20tempered%20my%20advice%20with%20this%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGiving%20money%20to%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20the%20case%20of%20a%20reader%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgave-son-money-no-strings-attached-husband-wants-pay-2023-12%5C%22%3Egave%20their%20son%20%2416%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20now%20feels%20pressured%20by%20their%20spouse%20to%20seek%20repayment%2C%20I%20had%20no%20experiences%20to%20compare%20it%20to.%20However%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20know%20how%20it%20feels%20to%20be%20caught%20between%20loved%20ones%2C%20pressured%20on%20both%20sides%20to%20appease%20one%20at