ng%20an%20addiction.%20Though%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-break-social-media-addiction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esocial%20media%20addictions%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20aren't%20considered%20the%20same%20as%20serious%20addictions%20such%20as%20drugs%20or%20alcohol%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.addictioncenter.com%2Fdrugs%2Fsocial-media-addiction%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520a%2520new%2520study%2Cpathways%2520affect%2520decisions%2520and%2520sensations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethey%20change%20the%20balance%20of%20chemicals%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20your%20brain%20in%20the%20same%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20actually%20experienced%20relapses%2C%20which%20might%20seem%20surprising.%20But%20I%20would%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20re-download%20one%20of%20the%20apps.%20Or%20log%20on%20my%20laptop.%20It%20took%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20cut%20it%20out%20altogether%2C%20and%20often%2C%20I'd%20have%20to%20use%20special%20apps%20that%20locked%20me%20out%20of%20my%20phone%20or%20blocked%20software%20on%20my%20laptop.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20seemed%20ridiculous%20that%20quitting%20these%20apps%20was%20such%20hard%20work.%20But%20having%20gone%20through%20it%2C%20it's%20been%20absolutely%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20change%20in%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-calm-anxiety%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eanxiety%20levels%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20been%20particularly%20noticeable.%20I'm%20not%20suggesting%20it's%20a%20cure%20for%20anxiety%2C%20but%20I%20now%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20know%20everything%20that%20everyone%20is%20doing%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstagra