ng-unique-numbers-to-eci%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20unique%20bond%20numbers%20would%20help%20match%20purchasers%20of%20the%20bonds%20with%20the%20political%20parties%20that%20redeemed%20those%20bonds.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsbi-submits-all-electoral-bond-details-including-unique-numbers-to-eci%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'What%20Is%20Your%20Governor%20Doing%3F'%3A%20SC%20Slams%20R.N.%20Ravi's%20Refusal%20to%20Re-Induct%20MLA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12172053%2FScreen-Shot-2024-02-12-at-5.20.18-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20criticised%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%20for%20refusing%20to%20re-induct%20lawmaker%20K.%20Ponmudi%20as%20minister%20even%20after%20the%20suspension%20of%20his%20conviction%20by%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Ftn-governor-defying-supreme-court-seriously-concerned-about-his-conduct-supreme-court-slams-governor-rn-ravi-for-refusing-to-appoint-minister-253019%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20reported%20that%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20took%20a%20dim%20view%20of%20the%20delay%2C%20and%20asked%20Attorney%20General%20for%20India%2C%20R.%20Venkataramani%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20is%20your%20governor%20doing%3F%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20conviction%20has%20been%20stayed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20Governor%20says%20he%20won%E2%80%99t%20swear%20him%20in!%20We%20will%20have%20to%20make%20some%20serious%20observations.%20Please%20tell%20your%20governor%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20take%20a%20serious%20view%20of%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20also%20asked%20as%20to%20how%20a%20governor%20can%20say%20%E2%80%93%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20stayed%20the%20MLA%E2%80%99s%20conviction%20%E2%80%93%20that%20%E2%80%9Chis%20reinduction%20as%20a%20Minister%20will%20be%20against%20Constitutional%20Morality.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%2C%20also%20consisting%20of%20Justice%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20was%20hearing%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20seeking%20a%20direction%20to%20the%20governor%20to%20accept%20the%20recommendation%20made%20by%20chief%20minister%20M.K.%20Stalin%20to%20reappoint%20Ponmudi%20as%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20situation%20had%20constrained%20the%20court%20to%20express%20serious%20concern%20about%20the%20governor%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20did%20not%20want%20to%20say%20it%20out%20loud%20in%20court%20but%20you%20are%20now%20constraining%20us%20to%20say%20that%20aloud.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20way.%20He%20is%20defying%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stressed%20that%20when%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20stays%20a%20conviction%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Governor%20has%20no%20business%20to%20tell%20us%20that%20this%20does%20not%20wipe%20off%20the%20conviction%20and%20it%20is%20non-existent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20also%20added%20that%20this%20means%20that%20those%20who%20have%20advised%20Governor%20Ravi%20have%20not%20done%20so%20%E2%80%9Ccorrectly%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AG%20has%20sought%20time%20till%20tomorrow%2C%20March%2022%2C%20to%20respond.%20The%20court%20was%20stern%20in%20stressing%20that%20this%20deadline%20needs%20to%20be%20maintained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPast%20conflicts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavi%20has%20had%20several%20run-ins%20with%20DMK-led%20Tamil%20Nadu%20in%20the%20past.%20%3Cspan