block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Mud%20and%20fingers%20are%20our%20USP%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20records%20of%20when%20Oraon%20paintings%20originated.%20Sumanti%20says%20the%20paintings%20are%20several%20centuries%20old%20and%20were%20passed%20down%20from%20one%20generation%20to%20another.%20She%20grew%20up%20seeing%20her%20family%2C%20relatives%2C%20and%20neighbours%20do%20Oraon%20painting%20on%20the%20walls%20on%20various%20occasions%20in%20the%20Jashpur%20district%20of%20Chhattisgarh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCalendars%20did%20not%20exist%20for%20me.%20I%20could%20tell%20which%20month%20or%20festival%20was%20coming%20up%20based%20on%20the%20painting%20my%20mother%20did%20on%20our%20house%20walls.%20For%20instance%2C%20people%20would%20draw%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekaram%20%3C%2Fem%3Etree%20%3Cem%3E(Nauclea%20Parvifolia)%3C%2Fem%3E%20ahead%20of%20the%20harvest%20festival.%20Drawing%20an%20egg%20in%20between%20rice%20grains%20meant%20%3Cem%3EDanda%20Kattna%3C%2Fem%3E%20pooja%20for%20auspicious%20activities%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20peculiar%20thing%20about%20Oraon%20paintings%20is%20that%20mud%20forms%20the%20main%20base%20due%20to%20the%20availability%20of%20various%20types%20of%20soils.%20The%20community%20creates%20different%20shades%20of%20black%2C%20brown%20and%20red%20from%20the%20soil.%20Green%20and%20white%20colours%20are%20made%20from%20leaves%20and%20rice%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumanti%20says%20she%20adds%20glue%20to%20the%20colours%20so%20that%20it%20sticks%20to%20the%20canvas.%20To%20date%2C%20she%20and%20the%20people%20from%20her%20village%20have%20not%20used%20acrylic%20or%20synthetic%20colours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20mentions%20two%20reasons%20for%20this%2C%20%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20accessibility%20and%20cost%20came%20in%20the%20way%2C%20and%20secondly%2C%20natural%20colours%20are%20a%20very%20important%20part%20of%20our%20identity.%20Our%20ancestors%20were%20confined%20to%20villages%2C%20so%20they%20made%20natural%20colours%20on%20their%20own%20and%20took%20pride%20in%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EColours%20that%20come%20from%20the%20soil%20are%20seen%20as%20sacred%2C%20she%20informs.%20The%20elders%20of%20the%20house%20perform%20a%20brief%20ritual%2C%20praying%20for%20an%20obstacle-free%20search%20for%20the%20right%20soil.%20While%20red%20and%20brown%20soils%20were%20readily%20accessible%2C%20finding%20black%20ones%20was%20challenging%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20ancestors%20would%20have%20to%20dig%20in%20forests%20to%20find%20the%20black%20soil.%20The%20rarity%20factor%20makes%20the%20soil%20so%20important%20in%20our%20culture.%20Besides%2C%20these%20three%20colours%20are%20used%20in%20all%20our%20%3Cem%3Epujas%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20date.%20According%20to%20a%20legend%2C%20Mahadev%20and%20Parvati%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%20told%20our%20ancestors%20to%20use%20these%20colours%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20colours%2C%20the%20primary%20themes%20also%20remain%20intact%20in%20the%20Oraon%20paintings.%20Mostly%2C%20the%20paintings%20depict%20community%20life%20%E2%80%94%20including%20their%20dance%2C%20customs%2C%20forest%20deities%20and%20festivals.%20The%20making%20can%20take%20up%20to%2010%20to%2015%20days%20due%20to%20the%20layered%20process.%20Each%20layer%20has%20to%20dry%20before%20the%20second%20layer%20is%20completed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20the%20paintings%2C%20Sumanti%20uses%20her%20fingers%20and%20cloth%20(for%20dabbing)%20even%20though%20the%20use%20of%20a%20brush%20is%20slowly%20penetrating%20the%20community%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20mud%20and%20fingers%20are%20our%20USP%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20factors%20are%20what%20makes%20art%20so%20much%20more%20valuable%20and%20personal.%20The%20paintings%20do%20not%20preach%20or%20tell%20how%20one%20should%20live.%20Instead%2C%20it%20depicts%20Oraon%E2%80%99s%20culture%20most%20honestly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E